<br>
I'd definately look at a Skald/Skald or Skald/Zerker combo. Zerkers with Skald Damage add is flat out nasty. <br>
<br>
But the main reason you will want your wife to play a skald as well is so she can have just as much fun as youre going to have. Skalds rock. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uxumten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xumten</A> at: 5/8/02 11:38:16 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/usylla.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sylla</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/8/02 12:34:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best duo partner for a Skald?</span><hr size=1> Skald/Zerker is an powerful combo. As a duo, there is little worry about &quot;adds&quot;. With the offensive power of the zerker augmented by damage add, you can easily hunt reds. <br>
<br>
On the subject of RvR groups, has anyone grouped with hunters? I have yet to try it but I think the combo of a skald and a couple of hunters would make a great strike team. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/udaocobserver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DAoC Observer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/8/02 6:58:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best duo partner for a Skald?</span><hr size=1> What great advice...thanks, everyone! So far my wife and I have leveled a Skald and a Healer up to 12, and...um...it's sure a lot more pleasant than leveling a Hibernian Druid/Champion team. A lot a lot. Seriously, what's UP with Hibernia? It coulda been so cool, and instead it's an endless golf course. And the melee fighters (Spear Heroes excepted) are about as scary as caddies.<br>
<br>
Still, I'm thinking about bringing a Berserker up to 12, just to give the ol' infinite-damage combo a try, and maybe taking a Dark-spec Spiritmaster out for a ramble too. So any further stories of your experiences with Skald duoing would be well-appreciated.<br>
<br>
Love these boards!<br>
<br>
- Corvus Sable, 12 Norse Skald, Nimue<br>
<br>
(Yeah, I know Midgard's already kicking butt on Nimue, but it was the last RP server I hadn't used already) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=etzel>Etzel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/9/02 3:48:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best duo partner for a Skald?</span><hr size=1> A healer is fun for a while but having played one to early 30's it gets old real quick. The little things annoy you, having to be permanently anon once you pass lvl10, fully buffing up in a dungeon get a bad add, run out and you're back to buffing again, always having to stand back in RvR watching others deal damage. I'm not saying your pair is bad but know the pitfalls before you expend too much time on one or the other, maybe you can alternate chars so that you both get to deal damage?<br>
<br>
On the positive side I say zerker or SB, if you are sure you'll be duoing 99% of the time i'd go SB with a full axe/left axe/poison template (skipping CS/Stealth because by default you'd need to be apart a lot of the time). If you intend to solo a little go 5 spec. Of course the quote that always sticks in my mind regarding skald/zerk combo is that 'the skald is the guided missile, the zerker the payload'....... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uvalcurtain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valcurtain</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.thelostempire.net/images/TinyCrux.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/9/02 12:11:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best duo partner for a Skald?</span><hr size=1> I agree with the Skald/Shaman combo. . .a couple DOTs on the mob make them die faster, buffs are a boon, and the heals during down time are great. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/upiechow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>piechow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/10/02 1:36:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best duo partner for a Skald?</span><hr size=1> I like skald/shammy combo, since I use 2 computers it works out well. <!--